content.text:
A union is defined using the `union` keyword. The syntax is:
```c
union name {
  type1 member1;
  type2 member2;
  // other members
};
```
- **union**: Indicates a union definition.
- **name**: The name of the union (e.g., `Data`).
- **type1, type2**: Types of the members (e.g., `int`, `float`, `char`).
- **member1, member2**: Variables within the union.
After defining a union, you can create objects of that type:
```c
union name variable;
```
All members of a union share the same memory space, so the size of a union is equal to the size of its largest member.

